name: Daylight savings time
summary: Daylight saving time is coming to an end this weekend. In the United States, clocks will be set back one hour on Sunday, November 5th. The change will mean that sunrise and sunset will occur an hour earlier. Some states, such as California and Washington, have already passed legislation to make daylight saving time permanent. However, these changes will not take effect until Congress passes a federal law. Until then, the twice-yearly clock change will continue. The end of daylight saving time can be a difficult adjustment for some people. It can lead to fatigue, irritability, and difficulty sleeping. However, there are some tips that can help make the transition easier, such as going to bed and waking up at the same time each day, even on weekends, and getting plenty of sunlight during the day.

name: Fortnite
summary: The headlines indicate that the popular video game "Fortnite" has been hosting a variety of new events and collaborations. The game has introduced a questline featuring Vice President Kamala Harris, as well as a map designed by her. Additionally, several musical artists, including Snoop Dogg, Eminem, and Juice WRLD, have taken over the game's battle royale mode in a chapter called "Remix." ESPN has also launched a football-themed island within the game, and the overall Chapter 2 Remix season has brought back the game's original map with modifications by various artists. The article from Polygon provides a detailed schedule and information about the season's end date.

name: Stephanie White
summary: Stephanie White has been named Head Coach of the Indiana Fever, leaving her position as Head Coach of the Connecticut Sun after two seasons. This move comes after a season of rumors linking White to the Fever coaching vacancy. White's departure marks the seventh WNBA head coaching position to open since the end of the season. White's hiring by the Fever reunites her with former Iowa standout Caitlin Clark, a key player for Indiana. White, a former Indiana Fever player and Indiana basketball legend, brings a wealth of experience to the Fever, including winning a WNBA championship with the Indiana Fever in 2012. White's sudden departure from the Sun has sparked speculation, with some believing she is the front-runner to become the Fever's coach. White recently broke her silence on her departure from the Sun, stating that she is excited for the opportunity to coach the Fever.
